          "Sequence of Answers",
          "[Knowledge Components for learner, Sequence of Previous Answers]",
          "BKT, while interpretable, has issues with convergence in local minima regardless of optimization technique. \n\nDKT and SAKT get better predictive performance but are not interpretable.\n\nGoodd interpretable approaches such as DLKT or Deep-IRT introduce interpretability because they separately moddel knowledge and difficulty, but they are “definitive” and lack probabilistic context. \n\n ",
          "Authors propose not a model, but a neural network-based optimization technique - OptiNN - that improves BKT. \n\n",
          "Observations with no skills attached were not considered. Missing values were filled with mode.",
          "BKT, KT-IDEM, ILE",
          "5-Repeated Holdout Method",
          "AST09\n\n{RMSE: 0.363 - KT-IDEM-OptiNN}\n\nAST12\n\n{RMSE: 0.426 - KT-IDEM-OptiNN}\n\nALG08\n\n{RMSE: 0.327 - ILE-OptiNN}\n\nBRI08\n\n{RMSE: 0.310 - ILE-OptiNN}",
          "Authors compare 3 well-known KT models: BKT, KT-IDEM and ILE on 4 distinct datasets. 4 forms of parameter optimization are done for each model. \n\nOptiNN optimization shows the best performance consistently across all experiments on models.\n\nVarying the psarameters of OptiNN shows some robustness of the model.",
          "Holdout method.\n\n"
        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Intelligent Tutoring System",
          "Next Question Being Correct",
          "Probability of Correctly Answering Question",
          "4217 ASSISTments 2009 students, \n3310 KDD-Cup Algebra learners, \n46674 ASSISTments 2012 students, 6043 Bridge and Algebra learners",
          "Not Applicable",
          "Sequence of Answers",
          "[Knowledge Components for learner, Sequence of Previous Answers]",
          "BKT, while interpretable, has issues with convergence in local minima regardless of optimization technique. \n\nDKT and SAKT get better predictive performance but are not interpretable.\n\nGoodd interpretable approaches such as DLKT or Deep-IRT introduce interpretability because they separately moddel knowledge and difficulty, but they are “definitive” and lack probabilistic context. \n\n ",
          "Also, they authors also propose TransformerKT to beat state-of-the art models in a hyper-parameter insensitive manner. ",
          "Observations with no skills attached were not considered. Missing values were filled with mode..\n\nBKTransformer is an extension of SAKT that also incorporates BKT parameters for knowledge component.",
          "BKTransformer, DKT, SAKT, BKT-EM",
          "5-Repeated Holdout Method",
          "AST09\n\n{AUC: 0.892 - BKTransformer, RMSE: 0.340 - BKTransformer}\n\nAST12\n\n{AUC: 0.695 - DKT, RMSE: 0.433 - DKT}\n\nALG08\n\n{AUC: 0.788 - BKTransformer & SAKT, RMSE: 0.321 - BKTransformer}\n\nBRI08\n\n{AUC: 0.833 - BKTransformer & SAKT, RMSE: 0.304 - BKTransformer}",
          "BKTransformer achieves close to state-of-art performance on most datasets, being only surpassed in AST12 by DKT.\n\n\n\n",
          "No full interepretability of attention networks.\n\n"
